OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 30 Mar to Wed 8 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure to the southwest of the
OL,7,FUK will likely be the dominant feature
OL,8,Ffor this period. This will lead to a
OL,9,Ffairly blocked pattern, with weather
OL,10,Ffronts rounding the high to affect
OL,11,Fnorthern parts at times, where wet and
OL,12,Fwindy weather can be expected. Further
OL,13,Fsouth, drier and more settled
OL,14,Fconditions are more likely, as frontal
OL,15,Fsystems weaken as they meet the high
OL,16,Fpressure. Through the period, high
OL,17,Fpressure is likely to spread across
OL,18,Fmuch of the UK leading to settled
OL,19,Fconditions developing more widely.
OL,20,FWhilst temperatures will be generally
OL,21,Fnear to or a little above average,
OL,22,Fsome colder interludes are possible,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fespecially in the north, where there
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fcould be some wintry showers at times.
